Job Title: Project Manager: Civil Engineering 

Location: Greenville, SC

Employment Type: full-time

Listed Skills: Engineering, Project Management

Description:
Salary: $65K to $90K
What is your perfect fit?Do you have a background in Civil Engineering or Construction Management and are looking to grow your career with one of the fastest growing companies in S.C.?If so, a great company based in beautiful downtown Greenville is looking to add a Civil Engineering Cost Estimator to their talented engineering staff!If that describes you, we need to talk!
What your future day will look like:Participate in Logistics & Civil Engineering projects by performing cost analysis and controlsWork with Engineering and other departments to prepare cost data/information for contract bids and proposalsOrganize and monitor project costs ensuring compliance with contract specifications and company policiesMonitor data trends and cost metricsInterface with suppliers ensuring contracted work is completed to satisfactory standards
Benefits Offered:Company offers a great benefits package!Medical, Dental & Vision Insurance100% Company paid basic life insuranceSTD & LTDPTO40K matching up to 4%
Type: Direct Hire
 To be a champion in this role, you will need:Bachelors Degree in Engineering or Construction Management1+ years of related experienceExperience in cost estimating & planning in the logistics/civil engineering fieldFamiliarity with MS Office including ExcelStrong communication skills-will routinely communicate with clients, suppliers and governmental agencies
We know you are more than a resume and understand your next career move needs to be the right fit! If this is your first time considering Godshall as your trusted partner, welcome! Once you have applied, we ask that you give us 1-2 business days to review your experience and skills. You will then hear back from one of our recruiting professionals on your next step.
If you are checking in to see what types of roles we have, please consider reaching out to your recruiter instead. We will happily update your file and make sure we are considering you for all roles your experience is a perfect fit for!
